#: ../source/contributing.md:5
msgid "Philosophy"
msgstr ""

#: ../source/contributing.md:7
msgid "FitTrackee was created specifically to completely avoid proprietary web platforms for tracking sports activities.<br />Workout files contain sensitive data related to location and health."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/contributing.md:10
msgid "This is one of the reasons why, for example, automatic synchronization of an account hosted on proprietary web platform is not integrated into FitTrackee.<br />For the time being, files must therefore be added manually or third-party tools must be used (or developed) for this type of synchronization."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/contributing.md:13
msgid "The other important point is that FitTrackee must be easy to install, particularly for use by a single user and without interaction, for which Python and a PostgreSQL/PostGIS database are sufficient.<br />Ideally, it should be possible to install it on low-resource servers such as the Raspberry Pi 4."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/contributing.md:16
msgid "Pull requests or feature requests must therefore take these points into account."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/contributing.md:18
msgid "Report issues, ask for features"
msgstr ""

#: ../source/contributing.md:20
msgid "If a bug is a security vulnerability, please refer to security policy."
